column5: Decided to go to Eugenia today instead of fighting the crowds on the weekend. Arrived at the launch at noon and fished till 4:30pm. I knew I would be working hard for any fish after last night's cold front. Paddled against the wind from the launch for 30 minutes to get to my weedbed. Wind was 25km/h and the high for the day was 20C. Found it very hard to plunk the weed pockets because of the strong breeze. Finally got a bite around 2:30pm. Landed this 16" largemouth on a 3/8oz weedless jig & large white grub.  There were about 12 trucks and boat trailers at the launch but I only seen two boats fishing, one jetski and one guy just flying on a sailboard. The wind was out of the north and I drifted back to the car without touching the paddle. Unfortunately I had no other bites all day.
not a bad fish still! man you're a troop.. going in a kayak in pretty high winds and knowing there was a cold front.. lol.. atleast you got a decent fish and some new fresh air..
wow man!  good on yeah for braving all the conditions and coming out with a nice bass!  cheers!
Pretty fish. One is better than none. Could be worse. You could've been at work. Hmmm, kayak and fish or work .......hmmm..................... tough one LOL.
Ya mon nice feesh bro. Hard work does pay off but a good day of trying anyway is always better than staying home doin squat, like I did....dang cast, dang thumb.
